sections.text:
Dried or dehydrated small cardamom may be:
- whole unopened capsules/pods: intact capsules/pods that have not lost seed;
- opened capsules/pods: capsules/pods with opening, not exceeding one-third of the suture’s length and containing seeds;
- seeds: seeds obtained after opening of the capsules/pods;
- powdered seeds: powder obtained from grinding cardamom seeds; or
- powdered whole capsule/pods: powder obtained from grinding whole/open capsules/pods with seeds.
Other styles distinctly different from those five are allowed, provided they are labelled accordingly.

